# Plan — Sanctuary: Worship Playback Engine

## Demo Concept
**"Sanctuary"** — a full-featured, production-quality worship playback engine that maps all 9 client pain points to live, working features. A worship team leads a rehearsal: they load a song, set a count-in, navigate sections, run stems through a mixer, and monitor click + guide cues — all in the browser, all sample-accurate.

## Demo Choice Rationale
- Prototype vs full: **Full** (richness 10, no trip-wires). Frontend-only Vite + React app; no backend needed. Self-contained, zero deploy friction.
- Every one of the 9 "areas needing attention" becomes a working, demonstrable UI feature — this is the core pitch: Michael didn't just fix bugs on a similar app, he built the whole stack from scratch in a weekend.

---

## Traceability Matrix — 9 Pain Points → Demo Features

| # | Client Pain Point | Demo Feature | UI Component |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Playback transport reliability | Sample-accurate multi-buffer play/pause/stop/seek via AudioContext + lookahead scheduler | `Transport.jsx` + `AudioEngine.js` |
| 2 | Section navigation behavior | Arrangement markers (Intro/V1/Pre-C/Chorus/Bridge/Outro), click-to-jump, A/B loop | `SectionNav.jsx` |
| 3 | Audio synchronization | All stems start at exact same `AudioContext.currentTime` via shared buffer start call | `AudioEngine.js` (shared timestamp) |
| 4 | Click track timing | Dedicated click stem, BPM-locked, beat-1 accent, metronome flash | `Transport.jsx` + `Scheduler.js` |
| 5 | Guide cue timing and triggering | Beat-quantized cue cards scheduled via `AudioContext.currentTime`, lyrics/section text | `GuideDisplay.jsx` + `Scheduler.js` |
| 6 | Stem routing and playback | 6 independent stems (Drums/Bass/Keys/Pads/Click/Guide), each through dedicated GainNode chain | `AudioEngine.js` + `Mixer.jsx` |
| 7 | Mixer channel behavior | Per-stem: volume fader, mute, solo (proper exclusive-solo logic), pan knob | `ChannelStrip.jsx` |
| 8 | Count-in functionality | Configurable 1/2/4-bar count-in: audio click beeps + animated visual countdown overlay | `Transport.jsx` |
| 9 | Audio engine stability | Clean AudioContext suspend/resume lifecycle; gain ramping (no clicks/pops); graceful buffer reload | `AudioEngine.js` |

All 9 addressed. Zero gaps.

---

## Feature Set (Richness 10)

### Hero: Sample-Accurate Multitrack Transport + Mixer
- `AudioEngine.js`: loads all stem buffers via `fetch` + `decodeAudioData`; creates per-stem `AudioBufferSourceNode -> GainNode (volume) -> StereoPannerNode -> GainNode (mute) -> masterGain -> destination`
- Play: all stems call `.start(audioCtx.currentTime + offset)` with the SAME timestamp — sample-locked
- Pause: `audioCtx.suspend()` + record `pauseOffset`; Resume: `audioCtx.resume()` + reschedule from offset
- Stop: disconnect all sources, reset offset to 0
- Seek: stop → recalculate buffer offset → restart from new position
- Master clock: `requestAnimationFrame` loop reading `audioCtx.currentTime` for UI sync

### Supporting 1: Section Navigation + Loop
- Song metadata carries an `sections` array: `[{ name, startSec, color }]`
- Section nav bar: labeled chips in track order, active section highlighted
- Click chip: seek to `section.startSec`
- Loop A/B: set in/out points via section start/end; scheduler loops transport at out-point back to in-point

### Supporting 2: Click Track + Count-In
- Click stem is a dedicated buffer (sharp transient); always stays in sync via shared start
- Count-in: before play, schedule N bars of click-only playback with animated beat counter (4...3...2...1...GO)
- Configurable: 1 or 2 or 4 bars via dropdown in transport

### Per-Channel Mixer (6 channels)
- Channels: Drums, Bass, Keys, Pads/BGVox, Click, Guide
- Per channel: labeled strip with color, volume slider (0-100, maps to GainNode.gain), mute button (zero gain), solo button (mutes all others), pan knob (-1 to +1 -> StereoPannerNode)
- Solo exclusivity: Web Audio "radio solo" pattern — all non-soloed channels muted at master-mute gain

### Waveform Display
- Canvas element; waveform drawn from decoded AudioBuffer data (downsample to canvas width)
- Animated playhead (rAF-driven, `audioCtx.currentTime`)
- Section markers overlaid as colored vertical lines
- Click-to-seek (map click X to `duration * (x / canvasWidth)`)

### Guide Cue Cards
- Song metadata carries `cues: [{ beatOffset, text }]`
- Scheduler pre-schedules `setTimeout` calls synced to `audioCtx.currentTime` (acceptable for display-only)
- Cue cards appear/fade over the waveform display area

### Song Library (2 songs minimum)
- Simple song-picker header: song title + key + BPM + time signature
- At least 2 songs in the registry, each with its own stem set, sections, and cues
- Switching songs: stops playback, loads new buffers (loading state shown)

