## Design Direction

**Stage console aesthetic** — what a worship musician sees when they look at Ableton Live or Loop Community Prime at FOH.

| Token | Value |
|---|---|
| Background | `#0C0C0F` (near-black) |
| Surface 1 (panels) | `#161619` |
| Surface 2 (cards/strips) | `#1E1E24` |
| Surface 3 (input/hover) | `#28282F` |
| Accent (active/playing) | `#F0A830` (warm amber — stage light) |
| Accent 2 (selected/focus) | `#4A9EFF` (electric blue) |
| Danger/mute | `#E05555` |
| Solo | `#F0C030` |
| Text primary | `#F0EFEA` |
| Text secondary | `#8A8A95` |
| Font — labels/UI | Inter (Google Fonts) |
| Font — time/BPM readouts | JetBrains Mono |

Layout: horizontal channel strips across bottom (DAW mixer view), transport bar pinned top, waveform + section nav in middle. Full viewport, no scrolling needed.

**Nothing from michaelwegter.com's design system appears in the demo CSS.**

---

## Build Architecture

Stack: Vite 6 + React 18, plain CSS with custom properties, no Tailwind.
`base: '/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/'` in vite.config.js.
Output: `dist/` copied to `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/`.

### Source Files (12 in `src/`)
```
src/
  main.jsx                     React root + AudioContext provider
  App.jsx                      Layout, song state, context provider
  engine/
    AudioEngine.js             AudioContext lifecycle, buffer loading, stem graph
    Scheduler.js               Lookahead beat scheduler; cue dispatch
  components/
    Transport.jsx              Play/Pause/Stop/Seek/Scrubber/Time/BPM/CountIn
    SectionNav.jsx             Section chips, A/B loop controls
    Mixer.jsx                  Render 6 ChannelStrips from stem config
    ChannelStrip.jsx           Volume/Mute/Solo/Pan per stem
    Waveform.jsx               Canvas waveform + playhead + section markers
    GuideDisplay.jsx           Cue card overlay, fade-in/out transitions
    SongSelector.jsx           Song library header picker
  styles/
    app.css                    Design tokens + layout (CSS custom properties)
```
Config/entry (not counted against src limit): `vite.config.js`, `index.html`, `package.json`.
Audio assets: `public/audio/<song-slug>/<stem>.mp3` — served as static files, loaded via fetch.

### Audio Source Plan
**ACTIVATED: Programmatic generation (no external stems).** Researcher confirmed no permissive, no-login worship stem packs exist — all require account signup. This eliminates all licensing risk.

- All stems generated via `OfflineAudioContext` at build time: click (sharp sine transient + beat-1 accent), kick pattern (tuned noise burst), pad (detuned triangle chord, long release), bass (sine oscillator), keys (bright saw + envelope), guide vocal (filtered sawtooth). Render to `AudioBuffer` objects in-memory, no file I/O needed — or render once and store as base64 data URLs in `songs.js`.
- Two songs: same stem synthesis engine, different metadata (BPM/key/sections/cues). Song 1: 72 BPM worship ballad (A, 4/4). Song 2: 132 BPM upbeat anthem (G, 4/4).
- Researcher confirmed CONFIRMED: same-frame `.start(audioCtx.currentTime)` = same audio block = sample-locked across Chrome/Safari/Firefox.
- Scheduler reference: Chris Wilson "A Tale of Two Clocks" (https://web.dev/articles/audio-scheduling) — 25ms setTimeout interval, 100ms lookahead. `Scheduler.js` implements this directly in ~50 lines vanilla JS inside the React module.

